service_requests.description:
Can you get Bike Path to move the bike stand from the North side of Queens Quay (a residential sidewalk area) to the South side of Queens Quay where they built that beautiful bike path along the HarbourFront Park area?   People either rent a bike and mow down pedestrians on the North side or Jaywalk (Jay-ride?) the bike over the lanes of traffic, streetcar right of way to get to the bike path.
It seems incongruous to put the bikes as far from the bike path as possible. Plus, there is a dead space alongside the North edge of HarbourFront Centre (235 Queens Quay W) where the bike stands will not block ANYTHING. People can rent and ride much more easily...
